Equations
Write mathematical symbols and equations using Latex.
Use the formulas below to calculate \(\hat{\beta}_1\), the estimated slope, and \(\hat{\beta}_0\), the estimated intercept.
\[
\begin{aligned}
&\hat{\beta}_1 = r \frac{s_y}{s_x} \\
&\hat{\beta}_0 = \bar{y} - \hat{\beta}_1 \bar{x}
\end{aligned}
\]

HTML Overview

InfoExample


HTML stands for hypertext markup language:

structures what is visible to visitors of a website:

text
images
links





&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
      h1 {color: red;}
    &lt;/style&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;This is a title&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;This is a header&lt;/h1&gt;      
    &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
       &lt;li&gt;This is a &lt;/li&gt;
       &lt;li&gt; ordered list&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ol&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

HTML - Declaration


HTML documents

always start with a declaration. This way, the browser recognizes the file.



&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
      h1 {color: red;}
    &lt;/style&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;This is a title&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;This is a header&lt;/h1&gt;      
    &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
       &lt;li&gt;This is a&lt;/li&gt;
       &lt;li&gt; ordered list&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ol&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

HTML - Elements and Tags


HTML documents

consist of elements. These are written between opening and closing tags.



&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; 
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt; 
      h1 {color: red;} 
    &lt;/style&gt; 
    &lt;title&gt;This is a title&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;This is a header&lt;/h1&gt;       
    &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
       &lt;li&gt;This is a&lt;/li&gt;
       &lt;li&gt; ordered list&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ol&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

HTML - Root


The html element represents the root (top-level) element of an HTML document:

all other elements must be descendants of this element
important children are the head and body element



&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; 
&lt;html&gt; 
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt; 
      h1 {color: red;} 
    &lt;/style&gt; 
    &lt;title&gt;This is a title&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;This is a header&lt;/h1&gt;      
    &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
       &lt;li&gt;This is a&lt;/li&gt;
       &lt;li&gt; ordered list&lt;/li&gt; 
    &lt;/ol&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

HTML - Head


The head element contains:

titles (in browser: bars and tabs)
style elements



&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; 
&lt;html&gt; 
  &lt;head&gt; 
    &lt;style&gt; 
      h1 {color: red;} 
    &lt;/style&gt; 
    &lt;title&gt;This is a title&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt; 
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;This is a header&lt;/h1&gt;       
    &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
       &lt;li&gt;This is a&lt;/li&gt;
       &lt;li&gt; ordered list&lt;/li&gt; 
    &lt;/ol&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

HTML - Body


The body element contains the main body of pages:

headers
paragraphs
lists
tables
images
‚Ä¶



&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; 
&lt;html&gt; 
  &lt;head&gt; 
    &lt;style&gt; 
      h1 {color: red;} 
    &lt;/style&gt; 
    &lt;title&gt;This is a title&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt; 
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;This is a header&lt;/h1&gt;       
    &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
       &lt;li&gt;This is a&lt;/li&gt;
       &lt;li&gt; ordered list&lt;/li&gt; 
    &lt;/ol&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

HTML - Lists
The &lt;ul&gt; tag introduces un-ordered lists, while the &lt;li&gt; tag defines lists items
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;books&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;journal articles&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

books
journal articles
reports







Ordered lists are introduced with the the &lt;ol&gt; tag instead

HTML - Containers
The &lt;div&gt; tag defines a section, containing one or often more elements:

CodeOutput



&lt;p&gt;This is an introductory paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;`div` style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this important division there are two 
elements, which are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;a paragraph, and&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;an unordered list.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;`/div`&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is the concluding paragraph.&lt;p&gt;



This is an introductory paragraph.
In this important division there are two elements, which are:

a paragraph,
and an unordered list.

This is the concluding paragraph.

CSS Syntax

InfoCode


CSS syntax consists of:

a declaration, with one or more properties and values








values are followed by a semicolon
property:value; pairs are separated by a white space






p {font-size:14px;}
h1 h2 {color:blue;}
.count {background-color:yellow;}
#count-sentence {color:red; font-size:16px;}

CSS Internal

InfoCode


CSS rules can be defined internally:

within the style element
as a child of the head element

Internally defined rules apply to all matching selectors on the same page



&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; 
&lt;html&gt; 
  &lt;head&gt; 
    &lt;style&gt;  
      h1 {color: red;} 
    &lt;/style&gt; 
    &lt;title&gt;This is a title&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt; 
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;This is a header&lt;/h1&gt;       
    &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
       &lt;li&gt;This is a&lt;/li&gt;
       &lt;li&gt; ordered list&lt;/li&gt; 
    &lt;/ol&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

CSS External

InfoCode


CSS rules can be defined externally:

css file needs to be saved & linked to the html document
defined with the the linked element and as a child of the head element







Externally defined rules

are saved in a file with .css extension
apply to all matching selectors on linked pages







&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; 
&lt;html&gt; 
  &lt;head&gt; 
    &lt;link rel="styles" href="C.css"&gt; 
    &lt;title&gt;This is a title&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt; 
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;This is a header&lt;/h1&gt;       
    &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
       &lt;li&gt;This is a&lt;/li&gt;
       &lt;li&gt; ordered list&lt;/li&gt; 
    &lt;/ol&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

